Screen Stream — Desktop App Phase: Requirements Q&A
====================================================
These questions/answers shape the desktop application (control-panel GUI,
AppImage/.deb packaging, history, start/stop, professional UI).

--- ROUND 1: Architecture ---

Q1. GUI tech stack?
    A1. Electron (web UI) — gorgeous UI via web tech, packages to AppImage,
        Node toolchain (~heavier bundle).

Q2. App's role relative to streaming?
    A2. Control panel / dashboard — starts/stops the server, shows status,
        URL, QR, PIN, logs and history. Viewing/controlling stays on the tablet.

Q3. Packaging / distribution for Ubuntu/Debian?
    A3. Both AppImage + .deb.

Q4. How should "clone → it's installed" work?
    A4. Local ./install.sh builds + installs on clone (sets up everything).
        (Also: record all these Q&A in this file — they shape the tool.)

--- ROUND 2: Behavior & lifecycle ---

Q5. Closing the window while streaming?
    A5. Ask each time — prompt "Keep running in tray" vs "Stop & quit".

Q6. System tray and/or start-on-login?
    A6. "Whatever you like" → include BOTH a system-tray icon (quick start/stop +
        status) and an optional start-on-login toggle in settings.

Q7. Default view simplicity?
    A7. Simple default + Advanced section (big Start/Stop + QR/PIN up front;
        quality/screen/port/TLS tucked under Advanced).

Q8. Most prominent connect info after Start?
    A8. ALL: big scannable QR, large readable PIN (with copy), URL + copy button,
        and a live "who's connected" indicator.

--- ROUND 3: History, logs, settings ---

Q9.  History records?
     A9. ALL: session timeline (start/stop + duration, first-ever/last-opened),
         per-session saved+reviewable logs, connections per session (IP/when/
         duration), errors/crashes flagged.

Q10. Storage backend?
     A10. SQLite in ~/.config/screen-stream/.

Q11. In-app log console behavior?
     A11. ALL: friendly status line + raw-log toggle, auto-scroll + color-coded
          levels, copy/export button, clear button.

Q12. Advanced settings exposed in GUI?
     A12. Security only — PIN mode (rotating vs fixed) + TLS on/off.
          (Monitors/quality/ports NOT in the GUI this phase.)

--- ROUND 4: Look & feel, portability, updates ---

Q13. Main-window layout?
     A13. Sidebar nav (Home / History / Advanced) — left rail switches sections.

Q14. Visual theme / accent?
     A14. Dark, indigo/blue accent matching the logo (charcoal surfaces,
          blue→indigo gradient accent).

Q15. Monitors on a different machine (e.g. dad's)?
     A15. Keep hardcoded for now (revisit display auto-detect later).

Q16. Updates?
     A16. "Check for updates" button — compare to GitHub latest release, notify,
          manual download (no auto-update this phase).

====================================================
BUILD PLAN (derived):
  • Electron control-panel app (sidebar: Home / History / Advanced), dark
    indigo theme, system tray + optional start-on-login, ask-on-close.
  • Home: big QR + large PIN (copy) + URL (copy) + live "connected" indicator,
    Start/Stop buttons (server does NOT auto-start), log console (friendly +
    raw toggle, color levels, auto-scroll, copy/export, clear).
  • Advanced: security only (PIN rotating/fixed, TLS on/off).
  • History: SQLite in ~/.config/screen-stream/ — session timeline (start/stop/
    duration, first/last), saved per-session logs, connections (IP/when/dur),
    errors flagged.
  • App manages the server: generates the PIN, spawns the Python server,
    parses logs + polls a new /status endpoint for live connections.
  • Two entry points unchanged + new: `screenshare` (CLI) AND the GUI app
    (double-click / app menu).
  • Packaging: electron-builder → AppImage + .deb. ./install.sh builds &
    installs on clone (venv, assets, build, menu entry).
  • "Check for updates" via GitHub releases API.
